# External Links (New Tab + Incognito Hint)

## Convention

- **Browsers cannot open links in incognito from a page.** Only the user can (e.g. right-click → "Open link in incognito window").
- For external bank/login or sensitive links, use a link that opens in a **new tab** and add a **tooltip** telling users how to open in incognito if they want.

## Pattern for such links

- `target="_blank"`
- `rel="noopener noreferrer"`
- `title="Opens in new tab. For incognito: right-click link → Open link in incognito window"` (or similar)

## Reference link in this project

- **Yono Business login**: `https://yonobusiness.sbi.bank.in/yonobusinesslogin`
- Used in: **Bank Info** panel (`BankInfoPanel.tsx`) as "Open Yono Business" with the above pattern.

## Example (React/TSX)

```tsx
<a
  href="https://yonobusiness.sbi.bank.in/yonobusinesslogin"
  target="_blank"
  rel="noopener noreferrer"
  title="Opens in new tab. For incognito: right-click link → Open link in incognito window"
>
  Open Yono Business
</a>
```

When adding similar external links elsewhere, use the same pattern.
